      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Doubling your water intake might help with the shakiness, but it's not a guaranteed solution. Lithium toxicity can occur if the balance of electrolytes in your body is disturbed. Stick to your doctor's recommended dosage and hydration plan. If you continue to experience shakiness, it might be worth discussing with your doctor for a possible adjustment in your treatment plan. Remember, it's always better to be safe and consult a professional rather than self-adjusting your medication.",
      "source": "target",
